    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In n(omine) D(omi)ni. Constat me <persName key="#Priests"><name
                                ref="Dominicus">Dominicus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">p(res)b(ite)r</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/80">s(an)c(t)ê <placeName
                                ref="#places/7">Bon(onien)s(is)</placeName> Eccl(esi)ê</orgName>
                        p(re)positus <rs key="#Monasteries">mon(a)s(terii)</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hospitals">exenedochie</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Hospitals">S(an)c(t)i(a) Donati</orgName> accepi
                        a te <persName><name ref="Leo">Leo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">p(res)b(ite)r</rs> ite(m)q(ue) s(an)c(t)ê Bon(onien)s(is)
                        Êccl(esi)ê filius q(uon)da(m) <persName><name ref="Leo/Petronge">Leoni
                                Petrogne</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Rent_in_money">pensio</rs> p(ro) sua por(cione) de reb(us) illis
                        in <rs key="#Fundi">fundu(m)</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Fundi"><geogName key="#Fundi"
                            >Salecto</geogName></placeName> et p(ro) <rs key="#Petiae #Hay/fodder"
                            >petia una terra q(ui) est prato</rs> in loco ubi dicit(ur) <placeName
                            key="#Petiae #Hay/fodder"><geogName key="#Petiae #Hay/fodder"
                                >Pulia</geogName></placeName>, quas p(er) <rs
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">enfiteosin</rs> tenetis ad iura
                        sup(er)scripti mon(a)s(terii), p(ro) om(ni)a sicut in ipsa enfiteosin
                        l(e)g(itur) <rs key="#Rent_in_money">d(enarios) duos</rs> p(ro) transactis
                        indicionibus q(ui)nta, sexta, septima, octava, NONa, decima, undecima,
                        duodecima et p(ro) p(re)sente XIII int(er) duab(us) ind(icionibus) <rs
                            key="#Rent_in_money">d(enario) uno</rs>. Unde p(ro) munimine v(est)ro
                        feci vob(is) h(oc) d(eaccepto) in m(ense) mar(cio), indi(cione)
                        s(uperscrip)ta XIIIma. Scripto p(er) manu <persName key="#Notary #Priests"
                                ><name ref="Iohannes">Ioh(ann)is</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">p(res)b(ite)ri</rs> atq(ue) <rs key="#Notary"
                            >not(arii)</rs> s(an)c(t)ê Bon(onien)s(is) Êccl(esi)ê. Dominicus
                        p(res)b(ite)r m(anu) m(ea) s(ub)s(cripsi).</ab>
                </div>
